Philippine Stocks: International Container, Philippine Exchange

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-04-14T04:48:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-14/philippine-stocks-international-container-philippine-exchange.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the noon close in Manila.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 0.7 percent to
4,234.96.  International Container Terminal Services Inc. (ICT)  ,
the largest Philippine port operator, climbed 3 percent to 49.50
pesos after Chairman Enrique Razon said the company will pay 50
centavos a share in dividends, the most on record. The stock
earlier jumped as much as 6.1 percent to touch the highest level
since the shares were first traded in March 1992.  Philippine Stock Exchange Inc. (PSE)  , the publicly
traded company that runs the bourse, surged 33 percent to 525
pesos, the sharpest gain since December 2003. The company
announced a dividend plan to give shareholders one stock on June
8 for every share acquired before May 25.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in  Manila  at 
